        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-08 15:53:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI question the semantics here.  Having all the methods synchronized will result in horrific performance.  Would it be better just to use a ConcurrentHashmap and be unsynchronized?  Also, if clients of CloudConfig are not expected to change the returned map, it should be returned using Collections.unmodifiableMap.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
